tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: Renal function is impaired, as indicated by elevated creatinine. Mild hyperchloremia and borderline high cholesterol are present. Liver enzymes and other electrolytes are within or near normal limits. Glucose, protein, and albumin are normal. No acute abnormalities detected aside from chronic kidney dysfunction and mild dyslipidemia; recommend clinical correlation and monitoring of renal function.
